            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add your <strong>meat-free mince </strong>(remove the paper if required!) to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown all over, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>While the meat-free mince is cooking, add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>black pepper</strong> to the pan (freshly ground is best!)</p><p>Tip: Try not to stir too often so the mince gets nice and brown!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1599749444615-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1599749444615-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1599749444615-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1599749444615-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1599749444615-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the meat-free mince has started to brown, add the <strong>diced pepper</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>chopped ginger</strong> to the pan and cook for 2 min further</p><p>Tip: Add an extra drizzle of oil if it's looking a little dry!</p><p>Add your<strong> mirin</strong>,<strong> hoisin sauce</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until thickened and sticky – this is your<strong> Chinese-style meat-free mince & green pepper stir-fry</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1599749453816-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1599749453816-x400.jpg",
